1184	The chain built in this chapter composes as follows. Čech acyclicity for the structure sheaf on basic-open covers yields the Čech-acyclic hypothesis. The comparison isomorphism between Čech and derived cohomology (a project-local construction, queued for a subsequent iteration) yields the $\HasCechToHModuleIso$ hypothesis. The existence producer of Theorem~\ref{thm:Scheme_hasAffineCechAcyclicCover_of_basicOpen} then assembles these into $\HasAffineCechAcyclicCover$, which the producer of Theorem~\ref{thm:Scheme_instIsAffineHModuleVanishing_of_hasAffineCechAcyclicCover} converts into $\IsAffineHModuleVanishing$. Together with the $H^0$ finiteness ladder of Chapter~\ref{chap:Cohomology_StructureSheafModuleK}, this closes Phase~A step~6 and delivers the genus carrier $\Module.\Finite\,k\,H^1(C, \mathcal O_C)$.

